- Good Lord, Diana, the implication.

1297
01:15:52,571 --> 01:15:53,974
- Damn the implication.

1298
01:15:53,974 --> 01:15:55,307
What girlfriend?

1299
01:15:59,186 --> 01:16:03,147
The story failed to spark
a scandal, thank God.

1300
01:16:03,147 --> 01:16:06,763
Perhaps everyone assumes
we are just close friends.

1301
01:16:06,763 --> 01:16:07,596
I hope so.

1302
01:16:08,719 --> 01:16:12,802
Anyway, James, we can't
let this come between us.

1303
01:16:14,020 --> 01:16:18,042
Unless, of course, your
other girlfriend already has.

1304
01:16:18,042 --> 01:16:20,884
(laughs) All right, James, all right.

1305
01:16:20,884 --> 01:16:23,619
I believe you, ex-girlfriend.

1306
01:16:23,619 --> 01:16:25,119
I believe you, I do.

1307
01:16:25,119 --> 01:16:27,952
(soft rock music)

1308
01:16:29,525 --> 01:16:32,701
Darling, I can't wait
for you to come home.

1309
01:16:32,701 --> 01:16:36,816
I'm playing our favorite
song and thinking of you.

1310
01:16:36,816 --> 01:16:37,649
- Diana.

1311
01:16:38,608 --> 01:16:41,695
You know I have no urge to
interfere in your private life.

1312
01:16:41,695 --> 01:16:44,540
- You've certainly made that
clear over the last 10 years.

1313
01:16:44,540 --> 01:16:47,217
Curious remark, don't you
think, coming from a husband?

1314
01:16:47,217 --> 01:16:49,566
- Nor do I have any desire to fight.

1315
01:16:49,566 --> 01:16:51,653
I truly want our
relationship to be amicable

1316
01:16:51,653 --> 01:16:53,451
for the sake of our children

1317
01:16:53,451 --> 01:16:56,400
and so that we can function
properly in our public duties

1318
01:16:56,400 --> 01:16:57,706
for the benefit of the nation.

1319
01:16:57,706 --> 01:16:58,836
- Charles, if you're
going to make a speech--

1320
01:16:58,836 --> 01:17:00,739
- I've known about your close friendship

1321
01:17:00,739 --> 01:17:02,256
for quite some time.

1322
01:17:02,256 --> 01:17:04,104
- I have many close friends.

1323
01:17:04,104 --> 01:17:06,981
Which one specifically
are you referring to?

1324
01:17:06,981 --> 01:17:08,231
- Major Hewitt.

1325
01:17:09,307 --> 01:17:12,236
I have reason to believe we can not keep

1326
01:17:12,236 --> 01:17:15,136
the proverbial lid on this much longer.

1327
01:17:15,136 --> 01:17:17,477
If it were to be made public, it would do

1328
01:17:17,477 --> 01:17:20,129
great harm to the crown.

1329
01:17:20,129 --> 01:17:21,470
From the evidence I've heard--

1330
01:17:21,470 --> 01:17:23,138
- Evidence?

1331
01:17:23,138 --> 01:17:24,305
What evidence?

1332
01:17:25,256 --> 01:17:26,782
Am I being spied on?

1333
01:17:26,782 --> 01:17:29,402
Are my phones tapped, what?

1334
01:17:29,402 --> 01:17:30,970
Am I supposed to install a shredder?

1335
01:17:30,970 --> 01:17:32,948
You certainly weren't
too careful about leaving

1336
01:17:32,948 --> 01:17:35,644
you love letters from
Camilla lying around.

1337
01:17:35,644 --> 01:17:38,307
Or did I forget to tell you
that I found them at Balmoral?

1338
01:17:38,307 --> 01:17:40,083
What colossal gall!

1339
01:17:40,083 --> 01:17:43,056
You lecturing me about being indiscreet.

1340
01:17:43,056 --> 01:17:46,332
- You're growing boldness is
making you reckless, Diana.

1341
01:17:46,332 --> 01:17:49,361
- I repeat, what evidence
have you, Charles?

1342
01:17:49,361 --> 01:17:50,444
- Audio tape.

1343
01:17:51,464 --> 01:17:54,047
You and the Major having at it.

1344
01:17:54,947 --> 01:17:55,780
- What?

1345
01:17:57,014 --> 01:17:59,016
And you listened?

1346
01:17:59,016 --> 01:18:00,807
- I'm aware of its contents.

1347
01:18:00,807 --> 01:18:02,886
- I want that tape, Charles.

1348
01:18:02,886 --> 01:18:04,457
- I didn't say that it
was in my possession

1349
01:18:04,457 --> 01:18:06,798
or that I would ever use it.

1350
01:18:06,798 --> 01:18:10,983
We're all vulnerable to
occasional breeches of security.

1351
01:18:10,983 --> 01:18:14,976
I was recently forced to put
a scrambler on my own phone.

1352
01:18:14,976 --> 01:18:19,209
It is my constitutional
duty to defend the monarchy,

1353
01:18:19,209 --> 01:18:22,363
to avoid any potential
embarrassment to the Queen,

1354
01:18:22,363 --> 01:18:26,251
and to use all available
resources in doing so.

1355
01:18:26,251 --> 01:18:28,500
- What is it that you want, Charles?

1356
01:18:28,500 --> 01:18:31,447
- I want you to end
this affair immediately.

1357
01:18:31,447 --> 01:18:32,280
- No.

1358
01:18:32,280 --> 01:18:34,102
If you want to lay blame for bringing down

1359
01:18:34,102 --> 01:18:37,352
the house of Windsor, look in a mirror!

1360
01:18:39,814 --> 01:18:43,901
I love James and I'm not
going to give him up.

1361
01:18:43,901 --> 01:18:45,401
Not now, not ever.

1362
01:18:53,482 --> 01:18:56,753
(car engine humming)

1363
01:18:56,753 --> 01:18:59,420
- [Photographer] Who's in there?

1364
01:19:01,755 --> 01:19:02,922
Oh, forget it.

1365
01:19:18,395 --> 01:19:22,768
- We're like an old
married couple, aren't we?

1366
01:19:22,768 --> 01:19:23,601
- No.

1367
01:19:25,353 --> 01:19:27,686
We still talk to each other.

1368
01:19:32,334 --> 01:19:34,299
- How I've missed you.

1369
01:19:34,299 --> 01:19:35,882
- That's my secret.

1370
01:19:36,937 --> 01:19:37,770
Stay away.

1371
01:19:40,215 --> 01:19:43,136
Can you believe I've been
in the service (scoffs)

1372
01:19:43,136 --> 01:19:44,523
17 years?

1373
01:19:44,523 --> 01:19:47,356
- And no one's named you Napoleon?

1374
01:19:48,727 --> 01:19:50,765
I'll have to raise an army

1375
01:19:50,765 --> 01:19:54,155
so you can have a proper command.

1376
01:19:54,155 --> 01:19:56,236
- Darling, we have to be realistic.

1377
01:19:56,236 --> 01:20:00,689
All my life all I ever wanted
was to serve my country.

1378
01:20:00,689 --> 01:20:02,584
Ever since I was a little boy,

1379
01:20:02,584 --> 01:20:06,167
all I wanted was to be
a soldier and now...

1380
01:20:07,864 --> 01:20:12,031
I'm just frightened it's
all going to be taken away.

1381
01:20:13,782 --> 01:20:15,955
- James, I know you're
worried about Charles

1382
01:20:15,955 --> 01:20:20,328
having that tape, but I have
some ammunition of my own.

1383
01:20:20,328 --> 01:20:22,078
He won't dare use it.

1384
01:20:22,976 --> 01:20:23,809
Darling.

1385
01:20:24,713 --> 01:20:27,619
We can't let this come between us.

1386
01:20:27,619 --> 01:20:31,286
- Diana, I could be
chucked out of the army.

1387
01:20:32,830 --> 01:20:36,760
(somber orchestral music)

1388
01:20:36,760 --> 01:20:38,997
What else do I know how to do?

1389
01:20:38,997 --> 01:20:40,414
Besides love you.

1390
01:20:42,752 --> 01:20:44,419
- But you're a hero.

1391
01:20:45,811 --> 01:20:48,065
- Quite the opposite.

1392
01:20:48,065 --> 01:20:51,469
If we're exposed, I'll be ruined.

1393
01:20:51,469 --> 01:20:52,802
And so will you.

1394
01:20:56,358 --> 01:20:58,358
You know that I'm right.

1395
01:21:01,332 --> 01:21:04,906
And you wouldn't want
William and Harry to be hurt.

1396
01:21:04,906 --> 01:21:08,406
(somber orchestral music)

1397
01:21:23,441 --> 01:21:26,358
(door clicks shut)

1398
01:21:27,281 --> 01:21:30,173
- The bulimic butterfly being
crushed on the royal wheel.

1399
01:21:30,173 --> 01:21:32,161
I mean, it's revolting.

1400
01:21:32,161 --> 01:21:34,714
Charles, you must let your
friends speak on your behalf.

1401
01:21:34,714 --> 01:21:37,721
- Hm, that was the first
idea proposed to me by staff.

1402
01:21:37,721 --> 01:21:39,780
But however emotionally appealing,

1403
01:21:39,780 --> 01:21:42,780
it's so distasteful, so undignified.

1404
01:21:43,793 --> 01:21:45,391
And the second idea was
that we should continue

1405
01:21:45,391 --> 01:21:47,416
as if nothing had happened.

1406
01:21:47,416 --> 01:21:51,217
But who would trust Diana to carry on?

1407
01:21:51,217 --> 01:21:52,431
- Honestly, I'm beside myself.

1408
01:21:52,431 --> 01:21:54,717
The book is unspeakable rubbish!

1409
01:21:54,717 --> 01:21:57,766
It paints you as cold and uncaring,

1410
01:21:57,766 --> 01:22:00,433
always putting duty before love.

1411
01:22:03,411 --> 01:22:06,900
- Clearly, I'm not incapable of love.

1412
01:22:06,900 --> 01:22:09,650
I'm just incapable of loving her.

1413
01:22:10,589 --> 01:22:11,862
- It's an atrocious pack of lies.

1414
01:22:11,862 --> 01:22:13,831
It's so unfair.

1415
01:22:13,831 --> 01:22:16,360
Did they propose a third solution?

1416
01:22:16,360 --> 01:22:19,163
- Yes, one that I quite like.

1417
01:22:19,163 --> 01:22:21,454
They're going to try to
increase my popularity

1418
01:22:21,454 --> 01:22:23,370
by promoting me as a statesman,

1419
01:22:23,370 --> 01:22:24,964
concentrating on global concerns

1420
01:22:24,964 --> 01:22:28,007
rather than an eccentric who's championing

1421
01:22:28,007 --> 01:22:31,112
old buildings and endangered
vegetables. (chuckles)

1422
01:22:31,112 --> 01:22:33,535
(Camilla laughs)

1423
01:22:33,535 --> 01:22:34,368
Who knows?

1424
01:22:36,129 --> 01:22:40,129
Perhaps Diana has unwittingly
done us a service.

1425
01:22:41,385 --> 01:22:42,435
Perhaps she'll end up forcing mother

1426
01:22:42,435 --> 01:22:44,518
to agree to a separation.

1427
01:22:45,673 --> 01:22:47,527
- By law, the Queen has
the right to strip you

1428
01:22:47,527 --> 01:22:49,988
of your title and your royal duties,

1429
01:22:49,988 --> 01:22:52,400
but the most onerous possibility of all

1430
01:22:52,400 --> 01:22:54,323
is that she has the power to dismiss you

1431
01:22:54,323 --> 01:22:56,183
as the mother of William and Harry.

1432
01:22:56,183 --> 01:22:57,183
- What?
- Mm.

1433
01:22:58,124 --> 01:23:01,172
In ironclad language known
as the grand question,

1434
01:23:01,172 --> 01:23:02,977
Parliament sets forth that the sovereign

1435
01:23:02,977 --> 01:23:04,963
has the right of supervision of the heirs.

1436
01:23:04,963 --> 01:23:07,068
In this case, the princes
William and Harry,

1437
01:23:07,068 --> 01:23:09,736
even during their parents' lifetimes.

1438
01:23:09,736 --> 01:23:11,256
- She can take my boys?

1439
01:23:11,256 --> 01:23:12,385
- She can.

1440
01:23:12,385 --> 01:23:13,557
She very well might.

1441
01:23:13,557 --> 01:23:14,989
We must keep this in mind when negotiating

1442
01:23:14,989 --> 01:23:17,156
your separation agreement.

1443
01:23:19,274 --> 01:23:23,191
If you want to take on
the Queen, count me out.

1444
01:23:24,440 --> 01:23:26,231
It would be no contest.

1445
01:23:26,231 --> 01:23:27,715
You'd lose.

1446
01:23:27,715 --> 01:23:30,318
- My children are my top priority.

1447
01:23:30,318 --> 01:23:32,292
I don't want to do anything
or agree to anything

1448
01:23:32,292 --> 01:23:35,119
that would jeopardize my access to them.

1449
01:23:35,119 --> 01:23:38,786
Without my sons, my
life isn't worth living.

1450
01:23:47,871 --> 01:23:49,863
- What on earth's going on?

1451
01:23:49,863 --> 01:23:51,826
- They've done it, it's official.

1452
01:23:51,826 --> 01:23:53,050
Prime Minister just
announced it on the tele.

1453
01:23:53,050 --> 01:23:54,905
They've separated.

1454
01:23:54,905 --> 01:23:57,471
Better try and hold on to
your job with both hands.

1455
01:23:57,471 --> 01:23:58,466
- But what's all this?

1456
01:23:58,466 --> 01:24:00,248
- Oh, his nibs is cleaning house.

1457
01:24:00,248 --> 01:24:01,863
Can't have their wedding presents turn up

1458
01:24:01,863 --> 01:24:03,518
at some flea market, can they?

1459
01:24:03,518 --> 01:24:05,207
- (scoffs) What a waste.

1460
01:24:05,207 --> 01:24:07,572
Selfish, every last on of them.

1461
01:24:07,572 --> 01:24:09,192
You'd think it might occur to them

1462
01:24:09,192 --> 01:24:11,908
the least they could do is
give some of this to the poor.

1463
01:24:11,908 --> 01:24:13,904
Not to mention their poor servants.

1464
01:24:13,904 --> 01:24:16,654
(fire crackling)

1465
01:24:22,831 --> 01:24:25,136
- Here's why I had to
see you straight away.

1466
01:24:25,136 --> 01:24:27,247
Andrew Morton phoned asking about you.

1467
01:24:27,247 --> 01:24:29,020
He's doing another book.

1468
01:24:29,020 --> 01:24:30,697
He wanted my to cooperate,
and of course I said

1469
01:24:30,697 --> 01:24:32,737
absolutely not.

1470
01:24:32,737 --> 01:24:34,741
- Call him back.

1471
01:24:34,741 --> 01:24:35,574
- What?

1472
01:24:36,600 --> 01:24:38,567
- Tell him you'll talk.

1473
01:24:38,567 --> 01:24:40,801
- Diana, are you quiet sure?

1474
01:24:40,801 --> 01:24:42,699
- I have to do something.

1475
01:24:42,699 --> 01:24:45,872
I'm fed up of being
portrayed as a basket case.

1476
01:24:45,872 --> 01:24:48,622
(engine revving)

1477
01:25:02,949 --> 01:25:05,449
(dog barking)

1478
01:25:12,485 --> 01:25:13,818
- You look well.

1479
01:25:15,209 --> 01:25:17,219
- Have you managed to find anything?

1480
01:25:17,219 --> 01:25:18,737
Work, I mean.

1481
01:25:18,737 --> 01:25:19,570
- No.

1482
01:25:21,905 --> 01:25:23,938
- Does your mother blame me?

1483
01:25:23,938 --> 01:25:24,771
- No.

1484
01:25:27,010 --> 01:25:27,843
- Do you?

1485
01:25:29,650 --> 01:25:31,848
- The army dismissed 1400 men.

1486
01:25:31,848 --> 01:25:33,732
I just happened to be one of them.

1487
01:25:33,732 --> 01:25:34,927
Diana, I have to tell you something

1488
01:25:34,927 --> 01:25:39,094
that you're not gonna like,
but I don't want you to worry.

1489
01:25:42,326 --> 01:25:46,493
The news about us is going
to break at any minute and

1490
01:25:48,655 --> 01:25:50,307
we just can't keep it secret any longer,

1491
01:25:50,307 --> 01:25:52,567
so I think it would be much better if

1492
01:25:52,567 --> 01:25:56,400
it comes out the way we
both know it happened.

1493
01:25:58,179 --> 01:26:00,679
I just hope you'll understand.

1494
01:26:01,534 --> 01:26:04,489
You had to tell your story,

1495
01:26:04,489 --> 01:26:07,489
I've had to sell mine to the papers.

1496
01:26:09,544 --> 01:26:12,127
This won't hurt you, I promise.

1497
01:26:14,401 --> 01:26:17,901
(somber orchestral music)

1498
01:26:29,204 --> 01:26:30,037
I'm sorry.

1499
01:26:32,859 --> 01:26:34,442
I'm terribly sorry.

1500
01:26:44,406 --> 01:26:47,804
(engine cranks)

1501
01:26:47,804 --> 01:26:50,887
(engine accelerates)

1502
01:27:10,168 --> 01:27:14,335
- My darlings, I wanted you
to hear this from me first

1503
01:27:15,651 --> 01:27:19,651
in case any of your friends
have said something.

1504
01:27:20,781 --> 01:27:22,059
There's this book.

1505
01:27:22,059 --> 01:27:23,476
- We know, Mummy.

1506
01:27:29,819 --> 01:27:33,486
They're chocolates, to
make you smile again.

1507
01:27:39,305 --> 01:27:41,388
(laughs)

1508
01:27:43,127 --> 01:27:46,658
(sentimental orchestral music)

1509
01:27:46,658 --> 01:27:47,646
- [Interviewer] A book published recently

1510
01:27:47,646 --> 01:27:51,610
claims that you were close
with a Major James Hewitt.

1511
01:27:51,610 --> 01:27:54,920
How would you characterize
your relationship?

1512
01:27:54,920 --> 01:27:57,612
- He was a great friend of
mine at a very difficult time

1513
01:27:57,612 --> 01:28:00,886
and he was always there to support me.

1514
01:28:00,886 --> 01:28:03,228
I was absolutely devastated
when this book appeared

1515
01:28:03,228 --> 01:28:06,482
because I trusted him
and because I worried

1516
01:28:06,482 --> 01:28:08,798
about the impact on my children.

1517
01:28:08,798 --> 01:28:10,510
- [Interviewer] Did your close friendship

1518
01:28:10,510 --> 01:28:12,982
ever turn into anything more?

1519
01:28:12,982 --> 01:28:14,649
- Yes, I adored him.

1520
01:28:16,117 --> 01:28:17,681
Yes, I was in love with him,

1521
01:28:17,681 --> 01:28:19,681
but I was very let down.

1522
01:28:21,023 --> 01:28:24,090
It was extremely distressing to me.

1523
01:28:24,090 --> 01:28:26,666
I felt very betrayed.

1524
01:28:26,666 --> 01:28:29,824
Sadly, the message is that ultimately

1525
01:28:29,824 --> 01:28:33,328
one can only depend on one's self.

1526
01:28:33,328 --> 01:28:34,900
- [Interviewer] What role do you envision

1527
01:28:34,900 --> 01:28:37,488
for yourself in the future?

1528
01:28:37,488 --> 01:28:39,655
Do you expect to be queen?

1529
01:28:40,701 --> 01:28:44,652
- I don't see myself being
queen of this country.

1530
01:28:44,652 --> 01:28:48,819
But I'd very much like to
be queen of people's hearts.

1531
01:28:50,321 --> 01:28:52,951
- [Narrator] After 15 years of marriage,

1532
01:28:52,951 --> 01:28:54,505
the Prince and Princess of Wales

1533
01:28:54,505 --> 01:28:57,183
are now negotiating a divorce,

1534
01:28:57,183 --> 01:28:59,022
bringing to an end the fairytale

1535
01:28:59,022 --> 01:29:01,854
that captured the
imagination of the world.

1536
01:29:01,854 --> 01:29:05,521
(dramatic orchestral music)

1537
01:29:09,767 --> 01:29:13,267
(somber orchestral music)

1538
01:29:57,077 --> 01:29:59,910
(MultiCom Jingle)

